[i][b]Middle Class:[/b][/i] [b][u]Everus[/u][/b] [i](eva-ress)[/i]

[ul][li]Mount Everus[/li]
[li]Eventurous[/li][/ul]


[u]Mount Everus[/u]
Setting: To be decided
Goal/Aim: Mount Everus is a 'Race to the Finish' minigame. In the minigame, you recieve points for each step you take. The points name are, of course, Everus Points, [b]and they may be used in the minigame only.[/b] There will be an item named Portable Everus Exchange. In it, the player may buy items such as barricades to block other users. Whoever reaches the top wins.
Reward: 20k + Misc.random(4,000)

[u]Eventurous[/u]
Setting: A far away island
Goal/Aim: Eventorous is propably the most epic minigame of these class minigames. You have seen this right?

[img]http://imageshack.us/a/img502/258/rs3lp5.jpg[/img]

Well, this will come to reality. The statues in the side are actually real monsters. It is up to the player to escape them. This will be team work. Here is a tip from me for this minigame:

[ul][li]Atleast 2 tanks[/li]
[li]Atleast 3 attackers[/li]
[li]Atleast 1 racer (A person who trys to get to the end of the island while the other monsters are distracted)[/li][/ul]


Of course, they won't be assigned. The team has to decide themselves in the waiting room.
Rewards: 10k + Misc.random(5,000) to every team mate.

[i][b]Middle Class:[/b][/i] [b][u]Demonica[/u][/b] [i](dee-mon-eca)[/i]

[ul][li]Demonic Dungeon[/li][/ul]


[u]Demonic Dungeon[/u]
Well, think of Demonic Dungeon as your [url=http://cs-portable.net/en]CS Portable[/url]. There are two things in this minigame.

[i]The Tutorial[/i] - The tutorial of course teaches you the basics of the game. The basics of the game are the following:

[ul][li]Being in the game gives you one point per 10 seconds. If you are in the enemy base then you get two points.[/li]
[li]There are multiple kinds of things that give you points.[/li][list]
[li][i]Normal Monsters[/i] - Killing a normal monster gives you either[/li][list]
[li]0 demonic points[/li]
[li]1 demonic point[/li]
[li]5 demonic points[/li]
[li]6 demonic points[/li]
[li]12 demonic points[/li]
[li]13 demonic points[/li]
[li]15 demonic points[/li]
[li]17 demonic points[/li]
[li]20 demonic points[/li]
[/list]
[li][i]Boss Monsters[/i] - Boss monsters are special monsters that, when they are spawned, the camera angle turns to them (This is actually unsure). Boss monsters give you even more points, points such as:[/li][list]
[li]30 demonic points[/li]
[li]60 demonic points[/li]
[li]70 demonic points[/li]
[li]140 demonic points[/li]
[li]170 demonic points[/li]
[/list]
[li][i]Staying In-game[/i] - If you are in the game you get one point per 10 seconds. You get two points if you are in the enemy base.[/li]
[/list]
[li]Use the points to buy weapons [b]IN-GAME[/b]! You may not use the points as a reward outside the game. If anyone may suggest items, we may give 'prizes'.[/li]
[li]Have fun! Enjoy the random monsters saying random, dumb things such as, "Who's the noob now," and such.[/li][/ul]

[i]The Game[/i] - Basically everything stated above.

